<p>Finally after much work and input from many folks, including and intense â€œ<a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20121026065214/http://www.mod.uk/NR/rdonlyres/B0558FA0-6AA7-4226-A24C-2B7F3CCA9A7B/0/RedTeamingGuiderevised12Feb10Webversion.pdf">Red Team</a>â€ (pdf) session at Boise State, I arrived at this draft:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Draft 5</span></p>

  <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Data Cairn is a platform for data storytelling, starting in Southwest Idaho, that allows communities to harness their data along with </span><strong>the work being done on it</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: relevant university research, government reports, local journalism, visualizations, public ideas and more, in order to discover and demand better solutions.</span></p>
